chael Rowe]]|s=David Wolf}}\n | OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1997|5|4}}\n | ProdCode=029221\n | ShortSummary= Matt and Joe nearly come to fisticuffs over Kristin, who is unable to handle the truth when she hears it; and Lou receives an e-mail message from an admirer.\n| LineColor=9400B6\n}}\n{{ Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber=39 \n | EpisodeNumber2=23\n | Title= Mother's Day \n | DirectedBy=Mark Cendrowski\n | WrittenBy=Craig Hoffman\n | OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1997|5|11}}\n | ProdCode=029222\n | ShortSummary=Mother's Day brings a surprise visit from Joe's hippie mom, who's pregnant and married to an \"aura-photographer\".\n----\nGuest stars: Jane Fleiss as Amber and [[Tom Kenny]] as Lucien\n\nNote: Tom Kenny previously guest starred as Doug in the season one episode \"Remember\".\n |LineColor=9400B6\n}}\n{{ Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber=40\n | EpisodeNumber2=24\n | Title=Girl Crazy\n | DirectedBy=Joey Lawrence\n | WrittenBy=Eddie Gorodetsky \n | OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1997|5|18}}\n | ProdCode=029219\n | ShortSummary=Julia returns hoping to strike up a relationship with Matt again, but his friends are not part of her plans. Meanwhile, Andy \"sells his childhood\" at a garage sale to earn cash.\n| LineColor=9400B6\n}}\n}}\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe show was first aired on [[NBC]] as part of its [[1995-96 United States network television schedule|1995\u201396 schedule]] and then switched to [[The WB]] for the beginning of its [[1996-97 United States network television schedule|1996\u201397 lineup]]. The show also aired in syndication on [[Disney Channel]] from 1998 until 2002. It has also previously aired on [[Family Channel (Canadian TV network)|Family Channel]] in Canada.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=3|1996\n| rowspan=3|[[Young Artist Award]]\n| Best Performance by a Young Actor\n| Matthew Lawrence\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Best Performance by a Young Actress \u2013 Guest Starring Role\n| [[Lisa Rieffel]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Best Performance by an Actor Under Ten\n| Andrew Lawrence\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n||1997\n||[[Young Artist Award]]\n| Best Performance in a TV Comedy \u2013 Leading Young Actor\n| Andrew Lawrence\n| {{Nominated}}\n|}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/19970415180002/http://www2.disney.com/DisneyTelevision/BrotherlyLove/_index.html Official Website]\n* {{IMDb title|0111901|Brotherly Love}}\n* {{tv.com show|brotherly-love|Brotherly Love}}\n* {{epguides|id=BrotherlyLove|title=Brotherly Love}}\n\n{{The WB Television Network}}\n\n[[Category:1995 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1997 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1990s American sitcoms]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by ABC Studios]]\n[[Category:American television series revived after cancellation]]\n[[Category:Television series about brothers]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Philadelphia]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the American sitcom|the British sitcom of the same name|Brotherly Love (1999 TV series)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Brotherly Love\n| image = Brotherly Love title.jpg\n| genre = [[Sitcom]]\n| creator = {{Plain list|\n*[[Jim Vallely]]\n*[[Jonathan Schmock]]\n}}\n| starring = {{Plain list|\n*[[Joey Lawrence]]\n*[[Matthew Lawrence]]\n*[[Andrew Lawrence (actor)|Andrew Lawrence]]\n*[[Liz Vassey]]\n*[[Melinda Culea]]\n*[[Mike McShane|Michael McShane]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Joey Lawrence, Michael Price, Steve LaGassick, Steve Barri\n| opentheme = \"No Matter Where You Are\", performed by Joey Lawrence\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 2\n| num_episodes = 40\n| list_episodes = #Episodes\n| executive_producer = {{Plain list|\n*Jonathan Schmock\n*Jim Vallely\n*[[Paul Junger Witt]]\n*[[Tony Thomas (producer)|Tony Thomas]]\n*Gary S. Levine\n}}\n| producer =\n| camera = [[Videotape]]; [[Multi-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n| runtime = {{Plain list|\n*approx. 22 minutes <small>(without commercials)</small>\n*30 minutes <small>(with commercials)</small>\n}}\n| company = {{Plain list|\n*[[Witt/Thomas Productions]]\n*[[ABC Studios|Touchstone Television]]<br>(1995-1996)<br>(season 1)\n*[[Walt Disney Television]]<br>(1996-1997)<br>(season 2)\n}}\n| distributor = [[Disney-ABC Domestic Television|Buena Vista Television]]\n| network = {{Plain list|\n*[[NBC]] (1995\u20131996)\n*[[The WB]] (1996\u20131997)\n}}\n| picture_format = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]])\n| audio_format =\n| first_aired = {{Start date|1995|09|16}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|1997|05|18}}\n}}\n\n'''''Brotherly Love''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[sitcom]] television series that ran from September 16, 1995, to April 1, 1996, on [[NBC]], and then moved to [[The WB]], where it aired from September 15, 1996, until May 18, 1997. The series was created by [[Jonathan Schmock]] and [[Jim Vallely]], and produced by [[Witt/Thomas Productions]] in association with [[ABC Studios|Touchstone Television]] (season 1) and [[Walt Disney Television]] (season 2). The primary focus of the series is on the relationship of three brothers, played by real-life brothers [[Joey Lawrence]], [[Matthew Lawrence]], and [[Andrew Lawrence (actor)|Andrew Lawrence]].\n\n==Characters==\n{{inuniverse|section|date=January 2020}}\n===Main===\n* Joseph \"Joe\" Roman (played by [[Joey Lawrence]]) \u2014 He is the oldest of the three brothers. He is a half-brother to Matt and Andy. Claire is his stepmother. He is vain, cocky and arrogant at times, and thinks highly of himself, though he is a good person at heart.  He is constantly fighting for the affection of Lou Davis. His brothers really look up to him as a role model and as a father-figure. He was born on November 10, 1975 as revealed in the episode \"Once Around The Block\" making him 20 years old at the start of the series. Joe was 5 when his father left him and his mother. His father eventually re-married Claire. Together they had Matt and Andy. Joe's father later died in a racing accident. Joe's mother lives in California. Joe is an avid motorcycle fan and works as a mechanic.\n*Matthew \"Matt\" Roman (played by [[Matthew Lawrence]]) \u2014 He is 15\u201316 and is the middle child. He bows to peer pressure easily. He is also put down by his family with some of his doings as well. Matt was an absolute neat freak and germaphobe; at the age of one, he could change his own diaper, and he went through his entire childhood without ever catching the chickenpox. He loved washing the dishes and was known for other odd habits like making \"Matt water\", folding his socks. Unlike Joe and Andy, he never did well with girls. He has a crush on Kristin and is said in the episode, \"I scream, You scream\", that Matt is in love with Kristen.  He sang twice, once in an angel costume singing the last two bars of \"Silent Night\" (A Roman Holiday), the other (Art Attack) when he played his mother's guitar and sang a song called \"Pigeon On Your Car\" which was written by Matt Lawrence himself.\n*Andrew \"Andy\" Roman (played by [[Andrew Lawrence (actor)|Andrew Lawrence]]) \u2014 He is the youngest. He is seen wearing a variety of costumes (including [[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]] and [[Spider-Man]]). He is a bundle of mischief and has a vivid imagination. In one of the episodes, he is \"in love\" with Lou Davis, and writes her an email. Andy was only 5 when his father died in a racing accident.\n*Louise \"Lou\" Davis (played by [[Liz Vassey]]) \u2014 She is a female mechanic who is seen going out with different men in a few episodes.  She is an artist, even having crafted a ring for one of her suitors.  She is always making sarcastic remarks to Joe from what he says about her. In later episodes it is shown that she may have love interests in Joe Roman. Joe and Lou kiss under the mistletoe in an episode called, \"A Roman Holiday\" and in an episode, \"Other people\". Andy is said to be in love with her, and receives an email from him, signed, A Roman who loves you. She automatically believes it was Joe.\n*Claire Roman (played by [[Melinda Culea]]) \u2014 She is Joe's stepmother, and Matt and Andy's mother. She is a take charge kind of woman and sometimes thinks Joe is a bad influence on Matt and Andy. \n* Lloyd Burwell (played by [[Mike McShane]]) \u2014 A former Coast Guard for six years and mechanic. He is overweight and is sometimes needy, but under his gruff exterior lies a sensitive, intelligent man. He used to go by the alias \"The Masked Avenger\", an alias he used to play pranks on Mr. Hangarter, a cruel drivers' education teacher. Lloyd is known to be somewhat stupid and ignorant, but in some episodes has surprised everyone and shown to be very intelligent.\n\n===Recurring===\n*Kristin (played by [[Rebecca Herbst]]) \u2014 She used to attend house parties often, but now has cleaned up her act. She is one of Matt's best friends.  She used to have a crush on Joe. Matt has a crush on her, but she sees him more of a brother than a boyfriend. She was a badgirl and got drunk, but changed after she and Matt started hanging out.\n*Silent Jim (played by Karl David-Djerf) \u2014 He rarely speaks but when he does, Matt describes it as \"something special\".  Instead of speaking he usually communicates with a laugh.  He is a recurring cast member, although, he does not appear in many episodes. \n*Myrna Burwell (played by [[Estelle Getty]], seen only in season two's \"Motherly Love\") \u2014 She is Lloyd\u2019s mother who lives in a trailer, and is part of the reason why Lloyd is so needy. She can do cartwheels despite her age. She also teaches the mambo and is said to clip Lloyd's toenails.\n\n== Episodes ==\n\n=== Series overview ===\n{{Series overview\n\n| color1   